title: For Sale:  Fine WWII Nazi Marked FN Model 1922 Pistol
postcontent: The first Model 1922 Pistols produced after the invasion used the Waffenamt stamp WaA613, from May 1940 until early 1941. This stamp is found on a very few Model 1922 pistols either manufactured prior to the invasion, or assembled from parts made prior to the invasion. These early WaA613 marked Model 1922 pistols were in both 9 mm (part of a 1940 Dutch order and some commercial production pistols) and 7.65 mm (assembled from pre-war parts). Only about 23,000 of these early marked pistols are known.

title: For Sale:  HK Heckler Koch SL8-1
postcontent: This is a fairly rare Heckler and Koch SL8-1 rifle. This rifle is, in effect, an effort to adapt the venerable HK G36 to the civilian marketplace. These were imported from 1998 - 2011 in their various forms. Whereas the G36 features a pistol grip and folding stock, the SL8-1 features a fixed thumbhole stock. Additionally, the SL8-1 rifle only accepts single stack mags (offered in 5, 10 and 20 round capacities) whereas the G36 accepts double stacked mags available in higher capacities. Other modifications have been made to the SL8 series of rifles including a lightened trigger pull, adjustable cheek piece and butt plate to customize the fit to the user, and a heavier, more accurate barrel. There are also a number of folks that have customized their SL8 rifles to resemble the G36, which of course, you have to option to do so with this SL8-1 rifle.......
